  "prompt": "How do low-income people survive in San Francisco with its high rent?",
  "response": "Low-income individuals in San Francisco often struggle to survive due to the city's extremely high cost of living. Some strategies they use include:\n\n1. Housing assistance\n- Section 8 housing vouchers\n- Subsidized housing\n- Shared housing/roommates\n- Living in less expensive neighborhoods\n- SRO (Single Room Occupancy) hotels\n\n2. Income strategies\n- Multiple jobs\n- Gig economy work\n- Working in service industries\n- Income-based assistance programs\n\n3. Cost-cutting measures\n- Using public transportation\n- Accessing food banks\n- Qualifying for MediCal (state health insurance)\n- Free/low-cost community services\n- Seeking nonprofit support\n\n4. Government support\n- CalFresh (food stamps)\n- Unemployment benefits\n- General assistance programs\n- Earned Income Tax Credit\n\n5. Alternative living arrangements\n- Living with family\n- Couch surfing\n- Living in surrounding more affordable areas\n- Vehicle dwelling\n\nDespite these strategies, many low-income individuals still face significant financial challenges and housing instability in San Francisco's expensive housing market.",
